						<div class="postbody">Has the NES scene decided upon a consistent and pseudo-official (say, NESdev official) set of names for all of the opcodes yet?<br /><br />Last time I looked, there were 4-5 variants for each unofficial opcode.<br /><br />If not, I'd strongly recommend doing so. I don't care what they are (so long as there are no overlaps; such that any can be specified distinctly with an assembler), I'd just like everyone to have the same name for each one.</div>

