						<div class="postbody">Another document you should be aware of is <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.ffd2.com/fridge/docs/6502-NMOS.extra.opcodes">http://www.ffd2.com/fridge/docs/6502-NMOS.extra.opcodes</a><!-- m --> . I used that one along with the one you linked when I implemented the unofficial opcodes. IIRC, the 6502-NMOS.extra.opcodes version tends to be correct for instructions where they differ.<br /><br />The instruction logic in nesalizer should be pretty easy to read if you don't mind looking at some code. Search for &quot;Core instruction logic&quot; in <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/ulfalizer/nesalizer/blob/master/cpu.cpp">https://github.com/ulfalizer/nesalizer/ ... er/cpu.cpp</a><!-- m --> . It passes Kevtris' and blargg's unofficial instruction test ROMs.</div>

