						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">address = (((high &amp; X) &lt;&lt; 8) + Y) + low;<br /></div>That looks wrong. Shouldn't it be <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">address = &#40;&#40;&#40;high+1&#41;&amp;X&#41; &lt;&lt; 8&#41; + &#40;&#40;Y+low&#41;&amp;255&#41;</tt>? <br />For example, if the sequence were<br />X=$FD, Y=$F0, <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.byte $9e, $f0, $01</tt>, what you have would write 0 to $02e0, but it should write 0 to $00e0.</div>

